<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="43" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,283,990]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,724,750]" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Discussion</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[458,704,724,749]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Peracchius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durantae">
<emphasis box="[458,704,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Peracchius durantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is unlike any other previously described whitefly, as defined in the generic and species descriptions, above. The distribution of this species will be modified by additional collecting in view of the wide distribution of the host plant in the Brazilian territory, and specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[766,905,844,869]" class="Insecta" family="Aleyrodidae" genus="Peracchius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="durantae">
<emphasis box="[766,905,844,869]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">P. durantae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have also been collected from an unknown host in 
<collectingCountry box="[473,551,884,910]" name="Belize" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">Belize</collectingCountry>
. Moreover, unidentified material from other countries in Central 
<collectingCountry box="[264,365,924,950]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">America</collectingCountry>
and the Caribbean appears to belong to this new genus (J. Martin, personal communication; material in Natural History Museum, London, 
<collectingCountry box="[1010,1057,964,990]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="4" pageNumber="43">UK</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
